# Email Prioritization Rules

Use these rules when classifying emails. They override generic heuristics.

## High importance (always)
- Emails from my-boss@example.com or cto@example.com
- Subject lines containing "urgent", "action required", or "deadline"
- Emails about production incidents or on-call alerts

## Low importance (always)
- Newsletters and marketing emails (unsubscribe links present)
- GitHub notification digests and automated CI/CD reports
- Emails where I am CC'd but not in the To field

## Medium importance (default)
- Meeting invitations that I haven't responded to
- Code review requests from teammates

## Special rules
- Any email from noreply@* addresses is low importance unless it contains a security alert
- Emails in languages other than English should be treated the same as English ones
